1.	Activity: Understand Types of components
1. Functional Component (Most Used )
Simple JavaScript function
Uses Hooks
function Welcome() {
  return <h1>Hello Student</h1>;
}
export default Welcome;

2. Class Component (Old Method )
Uses class and this
Has lifecycle methods
import React, { Component } from "react";
class Welcome extends Component {
  render() {
    return <h1>Hello Student</h1>;
  }
}
export default Welcome;


2.	Activity: understand Props
What are Props?
Props are used to pass data from parent → child
function App() {
  return <Student name="Aditi" course="Engineering" />;
}
function Student(props) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Name: {props.name}</h2>
      <p>Course: {props.course}</p>
    </div>
  );
}


3.	Activity: understand state concept with 2 examples
What is State?
State is used to store dynamic (changeable) data
1.
import { useState } from "react";

function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>{count}</h2>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Increase</button>
    </div>
  );
}

2.
import { useState } from "react";

function Toggle() {
  const [show, setShow] = useState(false);

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={() => setShow(!show)}>Toggle</button>
      {show && <p>Hello React!</p>}
    </div>
  );
}

